The paper proposes a novel face detection network with improvements in feature learning, loss design, and data augmentation. These are all key aspects of computer vision, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments involve benchmark datasets, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category, as face detection is often used in security applications.
